FBIS3-39708 "drweu035aa_94005" FBIS-WEU-94-035 Document Type:Daily Report 22 February 1994 INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS U.S. Reportedly Assures Grachev No Strikes for 48 Hours LD2002182794 Madrid RNE-1 Radio Network in Spanish 1800 GMT 20 Feb 94 LD2002182794 Madrid RNE-1 Radio Network Language: Spanish Article Type:BFN [Text] We now have a flash report that just arrived at our studio. Datelined Moscow, it says that on Sunday [20 February] the United States assured Russia that in the next two days Serb positions in Bosnia will not be attacked, despite the expiry of the NATO ultimatum at midnight GMT. This was stated during a telephone conversation by U.S. Defense Secretary William Perry with Russian Defense Minister General Pavel Grachev.
